.\" termin.al-name: pane
.\" termin.al-usage: pane split|focus|select|resize|close|zoom|swap|rotate|layout
.\" termin.al-summary: Manage terminal panes.
.TH PANE 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
pane \- Manage terminal panes.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
pane split|focus|select|resize|close|zoom|swap|rotate|layout
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Applies an explicit operation to the terminal workspace's pane tree. Pane focus, layout and content remain owned by existing workspace behavior.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ pane split horizontal viewer
$ pane focus next
.fi
.SH NOTES
Ctrl+b keyboard prefix behavior and responsive pane layout are not changed by this command's manual or by either manpager presentation.
.SH SEE ALSO
open(1)
